&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Linux Embedded Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a high-growth company seeking a versatile Senior (or Staff) Embedded Software Engineer to support vertical-specific customizations and platform stability for our production wearable systems. This is a hands-on individual contributor role requiring a generalist capable of navigating system boundaries—from kernel-level debugging to back-end logic and application tailoring.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate brings deep experience with Embedded Linux environments and physical hardware validation. While our next-generation architecture leverages the Go programming language, candidates with strong fundamental computer science and C/C++ backgrounds are highly encouraged to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Customization:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead technical alignment and vertical-specific applications deployment on our production Yocto-based Embedded Linux distribution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hardware Integration:&lt;/strong&gt; Support board bring-up and physical hardware validation using low-level protocols, ensuring seamless mapping from simulation to actual edge devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Architecture:&lt;/strong&gt; Collaborate across firmware and application boundaries, leveraging containerized runtime architectures (Docker/Podman) for Edge OS environment isolation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Code Optimization:&lt;/strong&gt; Debug and resolve multi-processor resource contentions across execution domains (CPU efficiency cores, DSP, NPU), emphasizing power management and thread execution priority adjustments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; Champion strict code quality standards, comprehensive version control processes (Git pull requests, cherry-picking), and early continuous integration pipeline validation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills and Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 6+ years of hands-on embedded software development experience, primarily with Embedded Linux distributions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systems Programming:&lt;/strong&gt; Command of C/C++ with strong computer science fundamentals, runtime architecture optimization, and pointer tracking knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Linux Infrastructure:&lt;/strong&gt; Solid familiarity with embedded build environments (Yocto Project, recipes, device trees) and low-level system diagnostic tools (GDB, strace, dmesg).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hardware Protocols:&lt;/strong&gt; Direct experience interface debugging with communication topologies, including I2C, SPI, UART, USB, and GPIO.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Workflow Tooling:&lt;/strong&gt; Advanced proficiency with Git, team collaboration development flows, and structural code reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred / &quot;Nice-to-Have&quot; Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Go Lang:&lt;/strong&gt; Prior experience with or conceptual familiarity with the Go programming language (concurrency, dynamic memory footprint tracking). Alternatively, background with Rust or complex multi-threaded architectures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Container Deployments:&lt;/strong&gt; Exposure to lightweight virtualization constraints and container orchestrations on target edge endpoints (Podman, Docker).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Power Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience profiling embedded execution workloads, process scheduling manipulation, and low-power constraint validation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior/Staff UX Designer will own the end-to-end user experience across BrightAI&#39;s product surfaces — physical hardware devices, mobile applications, and web dashboards. This role is responsible for translating complex product requirements into intuitive, cohesive interaction models that work seamlessly across form factors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is focused on the Stateful vertical and involves designing high-information density, configurable systems for B2B platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The designer will partner closely with Product Managers and Engineers to define interaction patterns, information architecture, and visual systems that make sophisticated AI-driven products feel simple and usable. As a senior/staff IC, this person sets the bar for design quality, mentors other designers, and shapes how design operates across the company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidate Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Skills (Required)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of UX design experience, with a portfolio demonstrating shipped products across multiple platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience designing B2B products and platforms, with a focus on data visualization, geospatial visualization, and visual experiences that are immersive and interactive.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing web portals or dashboards with complex data visualization, analytics, or infographics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mobile application UX experience across iOS and Android&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong systems thinking — ability to design coherent experiences that span hardware, mobile, and web without fragmenting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to translate ambiguous product requirements into structured user flows, wireframes, and high-fidelity designs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently, drive design decisions, and collaborate directly with Product Managers and Engineers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience defining and maintaining design systems and component libraries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Skills (Nice to Have)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing for AI-driven products or systems where outputs are probabilistic or generative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing white-label platforms where the UI adapts across multiple tenants or brands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with conversational, voice, or multimodal interfaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading design reviews, mentoring junior designers, or contributing to hiring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in industrial design, motion design, or front-end implementation is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing UX for physical hardware devices, including onboarding, connectivity, setup, and data flow interactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant startup experience (Note: Preference is for candidates with startup experience over those coming from large, non-startup companies).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deliverables Expected from the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;End-to-end user flows and interaction models spanning hardware, mobile, and web&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High-fidelity mockups and interactive prototypes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Information architecture and navigation systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dashboard and data visualization design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hardware onboarding and device pairing experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mobile app screens and patterns for iOS and Android&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribution to and stewardship of the design system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design specifications and close collaboration with engineering through implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Usability testing plans and synthesis of user research findings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BrightAI is a high-growth Physical-AI company transforming how businesses interact with the physical world through intelligent automation. We are building a cutting-edge AI platform that processes visual, spatial, and temporal data across billions of real-world events—from edge devices and mobile sensors to large-scale cloud systems.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a Staff Cloud Engineer (Architect) eager to take on the challenges of building the next generation of cloud-native applications and services in a fast-paced environment. You’ll work hands-on with cutting-edge technologies like drones, robots, industrial machinery, low-power devices packed full of sensors all communicating with cloud services. You’ll help architect and scale systems capable of processing hundreds of millions of events per day. In this role, you’ll have a direct impact on the design, scalability, and performance of our cloud platform, collaborating closely with world-class engineers as we continue to grow and innovate.&lt;/p&gt;
